-- Indonesian property firm Lippo Karawaci Q1 profit up 35 pct
-- By Eveline Danubrata
-- Wed Apr 30, 2014 04:47AM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, April 30 (Reuters) - PT Lippo Karawaci Tbk <LPKR.JK>, Indonesia's largest listed property company, reported on Wednesday a 35 percent rise in first-quarter net profit, lifted by its residential and healthcare units.

The company posted a net profit of 339 billion rupiah ($29.4 million) for the three months ended March, up from 251 billion rupiah in the same year ago period.  Revenues for its residential and urban development division surged 53 percent, while its healthcare unit saw a 29 percent increase in revenues.  Lippo Karawaci's business includes, residences, shopping malls, hospitals, hotels and asset management.